    "content_hash": "9a2eb5a3291385f5",
    "department": "Engineering",
    "description": "WHO ARE WE?\n\nEma is building the next generation AI technology to empower every employee in the enterprise to be their most creative and productive. Our proprietary tech allows enterprises to delegate most repetitive tasks to Ema, the Universal AI employee. We are founded by ex-Google, Coinbase, Okta executives, and serial entrepreneurs. We’re well-funded by the top investors and angels in the world. Ema is based in Silicon Valley and Bangalore.\n\n\nWHY DOES THIS ROLE EXIST?\n\nAt Ema, we are not just building an AI product; we are building an AI-native organization from\n\nthe ground up. Our mission is to serve as a model for the future of work, leveraging artificial\n\nintelligence to its fullest. We believe that the most valuable work is creative, strategic, and\n\nuniquely human. Everything else must be done by AI.\n\nTo achieve this vision, we are building an elite team of AI Application Engineers in the CTO’s\n\nOffice to bring this vision to life. This team will envision, design \u0026 build Agentic AI tools to\n\nfundamentally reshape how Ema operates - setting the bar for the post-AI era.\n\n\nWHAT IS THE ROLE?\n\nWe are looking for a foundational member for a transformative team aimed at revolutionizing Ema using Agentic AI. This role is about reimagining the future of work and then bringing it to life.\n\nYou will be a hybrid of product manager, strategic thinker \u0026 engineer, with a mandate to\n\nidentify and solve problem statements with Agentic AI to deliver impact.\n\n\nWHAT YOU’LL DO DAY TO DAY?\n\n\n1. AGENTIC AI TOOL BUILDING:\n\n● You will serve as the Product Manager, Designer \u0026 Developer in building AI-powered tools\n\nto streamline workflows for our teams and partners\n\n● Develop Custom Software: Build AI-powered micro-SaaS tools and intelligent\n\napplications to solve specific challenges across Ema\n\n● Leverage Modern AI Tooling: Utilize the latest generation of AI-native development\n\ntools (e.g., Cursor, Lovable etc.) and LLM frameworks to rapidly prototype, build, and\n\ndeploy valuable solutions.\n\n\n2. AGENTIC AUTOMATION:\n\n● Opportunity Discovery: Uncover problem statements for AI-driven automation across\n\nour processes and architect AI agents to automate the work\n\n● Deliver Impact: Leverage cutting-edge agentic workflow platforms—including our own\n\nEma platform in your journey to deliver value\n\n\nWHO WE ARE LOOKING FOR:\n\n● High Agency: You love to operate independently and autonomously to create outsized impact\n\n● A Builder at Heart: You have a demonstrable passion for creating things, whether it's\n\nscripts, full-stack applications, or complex automated workflows. You likely have a\n\nportfolio of projects you're proud of.\n\n● Product Thinker: You love talking to users and understanding their pain-points then\n\ndesigning solutions that suit them\n\n● A First-Principles Thinker: You don't just solve the problem as it's presented. You dig\n\ndeep to understand the root cause and envision a completely new, more efficient way of\n\noperating.\n\n● AI-Curious \u0026 Rapid Learner: You are fascinated by the latest developments in AI, LLMs,\n\nand agentic systems. You are not afraid to pick up new tools and technologies on the fly\n\nto find the best solution for the problem at hand.\n\n● Product-Minded: You have a keen sense for user experience and can build tools that are\n\nnot just functional but also intuitive and delightful for your internal customers.\n\n\nBONUS POINTS\n\n● Experience with no-code/low-code automation platforms (e.g., Zapier, Make, n8n).\n\n● Familiarity with agentic AI frameworks like LangChain, AutoGen, or CrewAI.\n\n● Familiarity with AI development tools (Lovable, Cursor, Copilot etc.)\n\nEma Unlimited is an equal opportunity employer and is committed to providing equal employment opportunities to all employees and applicants for employment without regard to race, color, religion, sex, national origin, age, disability, sexual orientation, gender identity, or genetics.",
    "employment_type": "FullTime",
